Date: 23/8/1862
Source: Otago Witness
Author:
Vol / Page: 4
Edition:
Quote: ... I am of the opinion that it is a payable gold-field. ... in the gullies on the west side of the Dunstan Ranges there was almost invariably gold obtained; ...  the prophets of ill ... have from time to time expressed an opinion that the Otago goldfields would soon be exhausted; that the area of payable country was comparatively small, and that in a short time it would be all worked out. ... he [a prospector with Californian and Australian experience] expressed his opinion that `Quartz Creek would turn out to be a payable gold-field;' ... <i>Ibid.</i> About twelve or fifteen miles below the junction ... we first obtained payable prospects. We tried a number of small bars that we thought would pay about an ounce a-day by working with a cradle.
